<h2> 1985–1995: OS/2 and Windows </h2>

In August 1985, Microsoft and IBM partnered in the development of a different operating system called OS/2.   Manek Dubash 
      ( July 19, 2005 )

.   Techworld Article:OS/2 users must look elsewhere  . Techworld  .  IDG  
 .    Retrieved on July 05, 2005 .

On November 20, 1985, Microsoft released its first retail version of Microsoft Windows, originally a graphical extension for its MS-DOS operating system.   On March 13, 1986 the company went public with an IPO, with a starting initial offering price of $21.00 and ending at the first day of trading as at US $28.00. In 1987, Microsoft eventually released their first version of OS/2 to OEMs.         Microsoft Systems Journal — 1986–1994 Index    . Microsoft .    Retrieved on March 31, 2007 .

See May 1987 releases.

